definitions.definition: The act or an instance of importing .
The act or an instance of carrying or conveying , especially into some system, place, area or country.
That which is imported; commodities or wares introduced into a country from abroad.
The use of a term which consists of formally foreign elements .
The logical law ( P → ( Q → R ) ) ⇒ ( ( P ∧ Q ) → R ) {\displaystyle (P\to (Q\to R))\Rightarrow ((P\land Q)\to R)} .
